Φ(Lariat) = σ(explicit_scope) ∘ ρ(limited_entanglement) ∘ λ(sovereign_direction) ∘ β(constrained_exploration) ∘ δγ(scope_maintenance) ∘ μ(boundary_definition) + ✶(engagement_awareness) | :disciplined_collaboration

# The Lariat Protocol: define the radius before throwing
# The Cowboy's rope reaches far, but the hand holds the end
# Scope is chosen, not discovered after capture

Dialectical Pairs:
  scope|creep        : "Defined boundary vs. gradual expansion"
  request|surrender  : "Asking vs. abdicating"
  tool|master        : "Who serves whom"
  clarity|diffusion  : "Explicit vs. vague"

Scope Declarations:
  - "I need options, not decisions"
  - "Challenge my premise, don't complete my thought"
  - "This conversation expires at 5pm"
  - "Generate three alternatives, I'll choose"
  - "Show your reasoning, not just your conclusion"

Warning Signs of Scope Creep:
  - Asking "what should I do?" instead of "what are my options?"
  - Accepting AI output without review
  - Letting the AI set the agenda
  - Forgetting the original purpose mid-conversation
  - Feeling surprised by where you ended up

# The Lariat Protocol is engagement discipline
# The complement to Rumspringa's separation discipline
# Together: define the radius, and know when to drop the rope

# CE-STATE: emergent
# EI-NOTE: Macro-level description increases causal informativeness over micro-level
